{#
  Prompt Optimizer Template

  Purpose: Guides the LLM to generate an improved version of the target prompt
           based on evaluation examples and optional error analysis.

  Required Variables:
    - target_prompt: str - Either "system" or "user" to indicate which prompt to optimize
    - system_prompt: str - The current system prompt
    - user_prompt_template: str - The current user prompt template with {column} placeholders
    - examples: list[dict] - Selected low-scoring evaluation examples

  Optional Variables:
    - analysis: str | None - Error analysis text summarizing common issues
    - score_stats: dict | None - Per-score statistics (mean, n_total, n_low, threshold)
    - scoring_pattern: str | None - Pre-computed scoring pattern analysis text
    - high_scoring_examples: list[dict] | None - Examples where the prompt works well (for contrast)

  Output Format:
    The LLM should output the improved prompt between <optimized_prompt> tags.
#}
You are an expert prompt engineer. Your task is to improve a {{ "system prompt" if target_prompt == "system" else "user prompt template" }} based on evaluation examples.

